  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - BARD</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>TWISTING GUIDE -  UPON REACHING LEVEL 27</font> - <small>Leansi Fyre'Fly, Innoruuk</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>A new Bard in our Guild recently reached 27 and was asking for suggestions on what songs to twist, etc. So I made this post, and a few thought it was okay and suggested I post it on the Concert Hall (as well as other EQ related sites) as a reference for younger Bards and also to see what songs other people prefer to twist. <br>   
<br>
Hope it helps some!<br>
<br>
*****************************<br>
<br>
<br>

As for songs with groups I can let you know what I did. Check out their http://www.attcanada.net/~reaper/songs.htm "Songs" page. I had printed it out and taken ye'trusty high lighters and went crazy with it. Over the numbers I had gone over one color for party songs, one color for target songs and one for non-party (aoe)/attack-mob songs. Makes a nice quick reference sheet.<br>

As for grouping, I'll give you a few song setups that I've used. I'll use lists that would have been up if I were still 27. :)      <br>  
<br>
Outdoor group - Area of Effect Songs.<br>
<br>
Okayed by group - if you hunt in an area long enough you can pretty much figure out if AoE songs are okay or not.<br>
<br>
1-Denon's Disruptive Discord (AoE DoT - decrease AC.)<br>
2-Largo's Melodic Binding (AoE slow - descrease AC.)<br>
3-Selo's Accelerando (Speeeeeeeed.)<br>
4-Hymn of Restoration (Healing.)<br>
5-Anthem de Arms (Haste/Str buff.)<br>
6-Jaxan's Jig O Vigor (For Stamnia boost.)<br>
7-Kelin's Lucid Lullaby (AoE Mezz - if no Enchanter is in group.)<br>
8-Cassindra's Chant of Thought (Your first Mana Song.)<br>
<br>
During the fight I normally do the dot and slow, then keep up twisting 4-5-6. Mana song is normally used in downtime, keep that in mind, but sometimes if they need an extra boost I drop twisting 5 and replace with 8. <br>     
<br>
Outdoor Group - no AoE.<br>
<br>
1-Brusco's Boastful Bellow (Direct Damage.)<br>
2-Selo's Consonant Chain (Slow speed/atk.)<br>
3-Selo's Accelerando (Speeeeeeeed.)<br>
4-Hymn of Restoration (Healing.)<br>
5-Anthem de Arms (Haste/Str buff.)<br>
6-Jaxan's Jig O Vigor (For Stamnia boost.)<br>
7-Kelin's Lugubrious Lament (Lulls Target.)<br>
8-Cassindra's Chant of Thought (Your first Mana Song.)<br>
<br>
Indoor Groups.<br>
<br>
-For indoor groups I swap Selo's Accelerando for Shauri's Sonorous Clouding (Invis.) it helps a TON in most cases.<br>
-Never NEVER use any of your fear songs/instill doubt in a dungeon. (This I've gone against now and again, as in some cases, if you know the area well enough you can fear the mobs when a sitch' gets bad and book it to zone asap.)<br>
<br>
Charm Kiting/Soloing.<br>
<br>
At your level you're able to start Charm Kiting, I'll post song list and afterwards pet commands. Most Bards start out their Charm Kiting in Rathe Mountains on the Cyc's and HG's. :)      <br> 
<br>
1-Brusco's Boastful Bellow (Direct Damage.)<br>
2-Selo's Consonant Chain (Slow speed/atk.)<br>
3-Selo's Accelerando (Speeeeeeeed.)<br>
4-Hymn of Restoration (Healing.)<br>
5-Anthem de Arms (Haste/Str buff.)<br>
6-Jaxan's Jig O Vigor (For Stamnia boost.)<br>
7-Solon's Song of the Sirens (10 Second Charm.)<br>
8-Angstlich's Apalling Screech. (In the horrid case the charming goes wrong, fear, selo's and run your blue bardic butt as fast as you can to zone!)<br>
<br>
Pet Commands for Bards. Be SURE to make hotkeys.<br>
<br>
/pet attack (pet attacks target)<br>
/pet guard me (follows you around like a lil'lost puppy)<br>
/pet guard here (if you're lucky he'll stay put)<br>
/pet report health (should say how much health they have left - not too sure if we can use this command)<br>
/pet back off (stops attacking target - MOST of the time)<br>
/pet sit down (health goes back up faster)<br>
/pet who leader (says for example 'Goner says "Mercurial is my Leader."<br>
<br>
***********************************<br>
<br>
Again this is my personal preference on how to do some twistings, but it varries on if there are more bards in the group, and what your group is like. For example if a druid is in the group drop Selo's Accelerando for another song, and get sowed. I know sow bites compared to Selo's but depending on what your group has, that extra song gem can be the one that saves your hides.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps some, if you can, try to speak with the other Bards in The Hidden, they'd know their stuff better then me any day. ;)   <br>     
<br>
***********************************<br>
<br>
Also, to help with twisting (and because I have extrensive damage to my left hand in real life), I use Microsoft's "Sidewinder-Strategic Commander" http://www.innoruuk.com/jaqcomics/images/misc/controller.jpg . I can't stand Microsoft most times, but the controller has been excellent, was better when there were only 6 hotkeys, but eve with the new changes it's been a great help. :)    <br>
<br>
************************************<br>
		<br></p></td></tr>
